<metal:heading fill-slot="pageheading">
  <h1>Launchpad graphics and icons</h1>
</metal:heading>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

  <p class="documentDescription">
    A summary of the icons and graphics used in Launchpad, what sizes they
    occur in, and what they mean.
  </p>

  <h2>Icon naming</h2>

  <p>
    We need a systematic and consistent way to name icons. At the moment, we
    just put whatever the name of the first icon we picked was straight into
    the templates. <b>Proposal:</b> we should use a name structure like
    "add_large", "add_small" and "add" to indicate the icons for "adding",
    with no reference to the file type (so, not "add.png") or size. Perhaps
    we should have "add_scalable" or "add_svg" to indicate scalable images.
  </p>

  <h2>System icons</h2>

  <p>
    These icons are used throughout the system, in all applications, and
    have the specific meaning defined here.
  </p>

  <table class="listing">
